Demonstrates @mf-toolkit/mf-bridge on the existing shell + catalog + checkout
MF stack. Remotes expose createMFEntry instead of bare React components;
the shell uses MFBridgeLazy with typed events, commandRef, retryCount,
timeout, errorFallback and debug mode.

Key interaction shown: clicking "Add to Cart" in the catalog remote emits
a productSelected event → shell forwards it as an addItem command to the
checkout remote → Cart updates. Placing an order emits orderPlaced back to
the shell → success toast appears. The "Clear Cart" button sends a clearCart
command from the shell to the checkout remote.

Each remote also runs standalone in dev mode (npm start without the shell).
