+### Scenario 5 — mf-bridge Integration
+
+The same shell + catalog + checkout architecture, now using [@mf-toolkit/mf-bridge](https://github.com/zvitaly7/mf-toolkit/tree/main/packages/mf-bridge) instead of raw `React.lazy`.
+
+**What changes on the remote side (catalog, checkout):**
+
+Each remote exposes `./entry` via `createMFEntry` instead of a bare component:
+
+```ts
+// checkout/src/entry.ts
+import { createMFEntry } from '@mf-toolkit/mf-bridge/entry';
+import Cart from './Cart';
+import { setCheckoutEmit, dispatchCommand } from './bridge';
+
+export const register = createMFEntry(
+  Cart,
+  ({ emit, onCommand }) => {
+    setCheckoutEmit(emit);                 // Cart can now emit → host
+    onCommand((type, payload) => {
+      if (type === 'addItem')   dispatchCommand({ type: 'addItem', payload });
+      if (type === 'clearCart') dispatchCommand({ type: 'clearCart' });
+    });
+  },
+  () => setCheckoutEmit(null),             // cleanup on unmount
+);
+```
+
+**What changes on the host side (shell):**
+
+`React.lazy + Suspense` is replaced by `MFBridgeLazy` with full lifecycle:
+
+```tsx
+// shell/src/App.tsx (key excerpt)
+const onCatalogEvent: TypedOnEvent<CatalogEvents> = (type, payload) => {
+  if (type === 'productSelected') {
+    // Forward as a command to the checkout remote
+    checkoutCommandRef.current?.('addItem', payload);
+  }
+};
+
+<MFBridgeLazy
+  register={loadCheckout}
+  props={{}}
+  fallback={<CartSkeleton />}
+  errorFallback={<p>Cart unavailable. Retrying…</p>}
+  onError={(err, retry) => setTimeout(retry, 2000)}
+  retryCount={2}
+  timeout={5000}
+  onEvent={onCheckoutEvent}
+  commandRef={checkoutCommandRef}
+  debug={process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production'}
+/>
+```
+
+**Event → Command round-trip:**
+
+```
+[catalog]  "Add to Cart" click
+    │  catalogEmit('productSelected', { id, name, price })
+    ▼
+[shell]    onCatalogEvent receives productSelected
+    │  checkoutCommandRef.current?.('addItem', payload)
+    ▼
+[checkout] onCommand handler → dispatchCommand → Cart.tsx useState
+    │  Cart renders with new item
+    │  User clicks "Place Order"
+    │  checkoutEmit('orderPlaced', { items, total })
+    ▼
+[shell]    onCheckoutEvent → shows success toast
+```
+
+**What you get for free vs raw `React.lazy`:**
+
+| Raw `React.lazy` | `MFBridgeLazy` |
+|---|---|
+| No error boundary | `errorFallback` + automatic reset |
+| No retry | `retryCount` + `retryDelay` |
+| No timeout | `timeout` with `AbortSignal` |
+| No events | Typed `onEvent` / `commandRef` |
+| No debug tracing | `debug` flag |
+| Module load only | Preload cache via `preloadMF` |
+
+**Running scenario 5:**
+
+```bash
+# Prerequisites: @mf-toolkit/mf-bridge must be published or linked locally
+# npm link @mf-toolkit/mf-bridge   (if working from source)
+
+cd scenarios/5-mf-bridge/apps/catalog  && npm install && npm start &
+cd scenarios/5-mf-bridge/apps/checkout && npm install && npm start &
+cd scenarios/5-mf-bridge/apps/shell    && npm install && npm start
+# Open http://localhost:3000
+```
+
